## Component Rules

- Create reusable components
- Keep components modular
- Follow existing Stitch component structure
- Avoid creating unnecessary new design patterns
- Extract reusable sections
- Keep components clean and scalable

## Styling Rules

- Use Tailwind CSS only
- Avoid inline styles
- Use cn() utility
- Maintain design consistency
- Keep spacing balanced
- Use subtle gradients
- Keep modern hover states
- Maintain dark mode support

## Animation Rules

- Use Framer Motion carefully
- Keep animations subtle
- Smooth hover transitions
- Avoid excessive motion

## Responsive Rules

- Mobile-first approach
- Responsive on all screen sizes
- Preserve Stitch responsiveness
- Avoid breaking layouts

## Frontend Data Rules

- Use mock data
- Use constants/data files
- Simulate realistic UI states
- Add loading skeletons when needed

## Code Quality

- Production-ready frontend code
- Clean architecture
- Reusable UI sections
- Maintainable structure
- Type-safe components

## Important

- Preserve Stitch design consistency
- Extend existing UI instead of replacing it
- Keep premium fitness brand aesthetics
- Focus only on frontend implementation
